				                <div><p>Hi Paul,</p>
<p>I had the same issue and was able to resolve it by making the following changes.</p>
<p>Change your function in the <strong>/theme/functions.php</strong> file to below:</p>
<pre class="cli" style="margin: -10px 0px -30px 0px;">function stop_heartbeat() {
global $pagenow;
if ( $pagenow != 'post.php' &amp;&amp; $pagenow != 'post-new.php')
wp_deregister_script('heartbeat');
wp_register_script('heartbeat', &lt;path_to_js&gt;."/dummy.js" );
}</pre>

<p>Please create an empty file <strong>dummy.js</strong> file in the <strong>&lt;path_to_js&gt;</strong> folder.</p>

<p>Basically, <strong>quickedit.js</strong> file seems to depend on heartbeat and hence, de-registering heartbeat disables it. This way, when we register heartbeat again as an empty file, atleast quickedit seems to work. Please try if the above works for you. Thanks.</p>

<p>Best,</p>
<p>Andy</p></div>
